<chapter xml:id="introduction">
<title>Introduction</title>
<simpara>Let&#8217;s implement simple internet store where you can create,
paid order and where system can change it&#8217;s state&#8230;&#8203;.</simpara>
<simpara><link xl:href="https://www.wiseweb.pl/blog-how-to-implement-event-sourcing-in-java/">motivation</link>
<link xl:href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Xu3Yn6Nx-iw">YouTube: KotlinConf 2017 - Why Spring Loves Kotlin by Sebastien Deleuze</link></simpara>
</chapter>
<chapter xml:id="implementation">
<title>Implementation</title>
<section xml:id="build-and-run">
<title>build and run</title>
<formalpara>
<title>build, run and test using gradle / docker</title>
<para>
<programlisting language="bash" linenumbering="unnumbered">./gradlew
java -jar build/libs/*.jar
bash build/libs/*.jar

./gradlew build composeUp
./gradlew composeDown</programlisting>
</para>
</formalpara>
<formalpara>
<title>build, run and test using maven / docker</title>
<para>
<programlisting language="bash" linenumbering="unnumbered">./mvnw
java -jar target/*.jar
bash target/*.jar

bash mvnw docker-compose:up -P docker
bash mvnw docker-compose:down -P docker</programlisting>
</para>
</formalpara>
</section>
